{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"62c6a5e1-c2db-41f1-86ee-af5703088310","content":"The template has the core required fields but has a few issues that should be addressed before publishing:\n\n**Issues:**\n\n1. **Missing `$schema`** — Add `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"` for validation support.\n2. **Missing `description`** — Important for NuGet discoverability; users won't know what this template does.\n3. **`choices` format is incorrect** — Should be an array of objects, not an object map:\n   ```json\n   \"choices\": [\n     { \"choice\": \"net8.0\", \"description\": \".NET 8\" },\n     { \"choice\": \"net9.0\", \"description\": \".NET 9\" }\n   ]\n   ```\n\n**Recommended additions:**\n- `groupIdentity` — helps group related templates.\n- `preferNameDirectory: true` — better UX when users specify `--name`.\n\n**Verdict:** Not ready as-is. The `choices` format will likely cause a runtime error, and the missing `description` hurts discoverability. Fix those two at minimum.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"087eb72c-1e22-4e7b-a6d5-4a4f32a68e97","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me review this template.json for NuGet publishing readiness. I'll check for required and recommended fields.\n\nRequired fields for a .NET template:\n- `$schema` - not present (recommended but not strictly required)\n- `author` - ✅ present\n- `classifications` - ✅ present\n- `identity` - ✅ present\n- `name` - ✅ present\n- `shortName` - ✅ present\n- `tags` - ✅ present with language and type\n\nMissing/issues:\n1. **`$schema`** - Not present. Recommended for validation: `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"`\n\n\n2. **`groupIdentity`** - Not present. Recommended for grouping related templates.\n3. **`precedence`** - Not present. Useful when multiple versions of a template exist.\n4. **`description`** - Not present. Important for discoverability on NuGet.\n5. **`preferNameDirectory`** - Not present but optional.\n6. The `Framework` symbol uses `\"datatype\": \"choice\"` with a `\"choices\"` object - I need to verify if this is the correct format or if it should be an array of objects instead.\n\nActually, looking at the official documentation more carefully, the `choices` field should be an array of objects with `choice` and `description` properties, not an object map. The format shown here is incorrect and needs to be restructured. I've identified three key problems with the template: it's missing the `$schema` field, lacks a `description` property that's needed for NuGet visibility, and the `choices` array is formatted incorrectly as an object map instead of the proper array structure that Microsoft's schema requires.","outputTokens":1031,"requestId":"7404:287A49:1B832A7:1E8F76B:69FA90E8"},"id":"f64f7d87-c9b1-4fb0-95ce-f7388396d75a","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:53:14.954Z","parentId":"5eddc7d4-81a0-4579-82d3-388779b0183c"}
